Sentencas: A 2D Model considering momentum, heat/species transport and electrochemical phenomena, has been proposed for tubular solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC

Sentencas: The model was validated using experimental polarization curves and the good agreement with the experimental data was attained.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC

Sentencas: The temperature distributions show that temperature varies severely at the tube inlet than at the tube outlet.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC

Sentencas: The heat generation and transfer mechanisms in electrodes, electrolyte and electrochemical reaction interface were investigated.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC

Sentencas: The results show that the overall electrochemical reaction heat is produced at cathode/electrolyte interface, and a small portion of the heat is consumed at anode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC

Sentencas: The heat produced at cathode/electrolyte interface is about five times as much as that consumed at anode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC

Sentencas: Over-whelming part of the heat transfer between cell and outside occurs at cathode external surface.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC

Sentencas: Most current flow goes into anode from a very small area where the current collectors locates.
Titulo: Numerical Analysis of Thermal and Electrochemical Phenomena for Anode Supported Microtubular SOFC
